# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: HollowWorld | Scene: TheHollowWorldMage1
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Seize my flask from the circle and move it behind the door."
    new "Seize my flask from the circle and move it behind the door."

    old "Near the cupboards, you will find another flask much the same as mine own. Replace mine in the circle with the fake flask."
    new "Near the cupboards, you will find another flask much the same as mine own. Replace mine in the circle with the fake flask."

    old "Sarah did as instructed, placing the spirit's flask in its hidden location."
    new "Sarah did as instructed, placing the spirit's flask in its hidden location."

    old "Her heart was racing. She knew there was no way back."
    new "Her heart was racing. She knew there was no way back."

    old "This is most crucial...where is the fate stone?"
    new "This is most crucial...where is the fate stone?"

    old "On his desk in the study."
    new "On his desk in the study."

    old "Run from here towards the study."
    new "Run from here towards the study."

    old "Do not stop, do not pause, do not speak. Seize the stone and immediately run back here."
    new "Do not stop, do not pause, do not speak. Seize the stone and immediately run back here."

    old "The mage will follow you, this I can promise you."
    new "The mage will follow you, this I can promise you."

    old "Once he steps into the room, he will be trapped between us."
    new "Once he steps into the room, he will be trapped between us."

    old "Together, our power might just be enough to hold him, but I warn you Sarah, he is most powerful. Do not treat him lightly."
    new "Together, our power might just be enough to hold him, but I warn you Sarah, he is most powerful. Do not treat him lightly."

    old "When do we do it?"
    new "When do we do it?"

    old "Now."
    new "Now."

    old "Sarah felt her heart freeze."
    new "Sarah felt her heart freeze."

    old "So fast, she couldn't imagine..."
    new "So fast, she couldn't imagine..."

    old "Why not wait, we can plan more, or..."
    new "Why not wait, we can plan more, or..."

    old "Every moment we risk the mage finding out."
    new "Every moment we risk the mage finding out."

    old "Now is the moment. We have laid our trap, we know where the fate stone is, and the mage might still be exhausted from his mission."
    new "Now is the moment. We have laid our trap, we know where the fate stone is, and the mage might still be exhausted from his mission."

    old "We strike now."
    new "We strike now."

    old "Sarah did her best to gather her courage. She was truly going to do this."
    new "Sarah did her best to gather her courage. She was truly going to do this."

    old "She threw open the door and exploded through the hallway."
    new "She threw open the door and exploded through the hallway."

    old "In little more than a second, she was in the study. She had snatched the fate stone off the table and was running back before even Xan fully noticed."
    new "In little more than a second, she was in the study. She had snatched the fate stone off the table and was running back before even Xan fully noticed."

    old "Sarah!!!"
    new "Sarah!!!"

    old "Get back here!"
    new "Get back here!"

    old "Sarah planted herself firmly in the center of the room, her heart was pounding in her chest."
    new "Sarah planted herself firmly in the center of the room, her heart was pounding in her chest."

    old "A few second later, Xan appeared in the room, slamming the door open so violently it bashed into the wall."
    new "A few second later, Xan appeared in the room, slamming the door open so violently it bashed into the wall."

    old "Have you lost your mind?!"
    new "Have you lost your mind?!"

    old "I warned you not to touch that stone! No, I explicitly forbade you from touching that stone!"
    new "I warned you not to touch that stone! No, I explicitly forbade you from touching that stone!"

    old "Ever since Bagrad, no, even before that, it's been one thing after the other with you!"
    new "Ever since Bagrad, no, even before that, it's been one thing after the other with you!"

    old "It just goes to prove what I said before, I should have taken you to the citadel a long time ago."
    new "It just goes to prove what I said before, I should have taken you to the citadel a long time ago."

    old "Hand me back that stone, I'm taking you to the citadel right now!"
    new "Hand me back that stone, I'm taking you to the citadel right now!"

    old "I told you I wouldn't go."
    new "I told you I wouldn't go."

    old "I told you, but you never listen to me."
    new "I told you, but you never listen to me."

    old "You think that just because you saved me all those years ago, that somehow, you own me, that I'm some thing you can order around."
    new "You think that just because you saved me all those years ago, that somehow, you own me, that I'm some thing you can order around."

    old "I studied magic so I could be free and powerful, not so I could be your slave."
    new "I studied magic so I could be free and powerful, not so I could be your slave."

    old "Xan stepped forward into the room."
    new "Xan stepped forward into the room."

    old "Well then you've made a very big mistake, because so long as you live, you're mine."
    new "Well then you've made a very big mistake, because so long as you live, you're mine."

    old "Every moment of your life has been carefully decided. There is a purpose for you, and I will make certain that you carry out that purpose. Everything else is secondary."
    new "Every moment of your life has been carefully decided. There is a purpose for you, and I will make certain that you carry out that purpose. Everything else is secondary."

    old "You're still not listening!"
    new "You're still not listening!"

    old "I'm not going!"
    new "I'm not going!"

    old "You don't get a choice! How many more times do I have to say this before you'll understand?"
    new "You don't get a choice! How many more times do I have to say this before you'll understand?"

    old "Xan took another step forward."
    new "Xan took another step forward."

    old "Sarah watched his eyes slide down to the flask."
    new "Sarah watched his eyes slide down to the flask."

    old "For a moment, he considered."
    new "For a moment, he considered."

    old "Then, she watched his eyes grow wide."
    new "Then, she watched his eyes grow wide."

    old "Xan had realized, but only by a fraction of a second too late, the truth of his situation."
    new "Xan had realized, but only by a fraction of a second too late, the truth of his situation."

    old "Razaphel leapt out from the flask, it's face warped and distorted, revealing rows and rows of razor sharp teeth."
    new "Razaphel leapt out from the flask, it's face warped and distorted, revealing rows and rows of razor sharp teeth."

    old "The spirit's mouth clamped shut on Xan's left arm with the force of a siege engine, cutting it off from the shouldr down."
    new "The spirit's mouth clamped shut on Xan's left arm with the force of a siege engine, cutting it off from the shouldr down."

    old "Xan screamed out at the injury."
    new "Xan screamed out at the injury."

    old "But he was fast."
    new "But he was fast."

    old "Sarah watched as his right hand began to glow with magical energy."
    new "Sarah watched as his right hand began to glow with magical energy."

    old "Xan raised his remaining hand, sending out a shockwave that slammed Sarah into the wall."
    new "Xan raised his remaining hand, sending out a shockwave that slammed Sarah into the wall."

    old "With the remainder of his power, he began to drive his burning hand into the spirit's body."
    new "With the remainder of his power, he began to drive his burning hand into the spirit's body."

    old "A wild screaming hiss emerged from Razaphel as it sufferd the pale fire."
    new "A wild screaming hiss emerged from Razaphel as it sufferd the pale fire."

    old "Making deals with this abomination, you're more lost than I thought."
    new "Making deals with this abomination, you're more lost than I thought."

    old "Sarah crawled back unto her feet."
    new "Sarah crawled back unto her feet."

    old "With energy swirling around her arms, she gatherd up her own magical fire, and began to unleash on Xan."
    new "With energy swirling around her arms, she gatherd up her own magical fire, and began to unleash on Xan."

    old "Even with one hand, she offered little challenge to the mage."
    new "Even with one hand, she offered little challenge to the mage."

    old "He deflected her attacks, weaving complex wards that Sarah had never seen before."
    new "He deflected her attacks, weaving complex wards that Sarah had never seen before."

    old "Only in this moment did she realize just how little she truly knew of magic, and how wide the difference between herself and Xan truly was."
    new "Only in this moment did she realize just how little she truly knew of magic, and how wide the difference between herself and Xan truly was."

    old "With a single motion, he released a barrage of energy towards her."
    new "With a single motion, he released a barrage of energy towards her."

    old "Only barely did Sarah manage to weave her own protective wards in time to deflect them. She could feel she would not survive many more attacks like them."
    new "Only barely did Sarah manage to weave her own protective wards in time to deflect them. She could feel she would not survive many more attacks like them."

    old "The entire house roared and trembled as the magical energies clashed."
    new "The entire house roared and trembled as the magical energies clashed."

    old "Their only advantage had been the sneak attack. But in an extended fight, she, even with the help of Razaphel, would prove weaker."
    new "Their only advantage had been the sneak attack. But in an extended fight, she, even with the help of Razaphel, would prove weaker."

    old "This had to end."
    new "This had to end."

    old "Sarah weaved her energy into a spike, all that she could bend and forge into it she did, and raised it up."
    new "Sarah weaved her energy into a spike, all that she could bend and forge into it she did, and raised it up."

    old "With a powerful throw, she released the spike of magical energy, slicing and cutting through all of Xan's wards, driving straight for his heart."
    new "With a powerful throw, she released the spike of magical energy, slicing and cutting through all of Xan's wards, driving straight for his heart."

    old "And he seized it from the air, falling short of his heart by an inch."
    new "And he seized it from the air, falling short of his heart by an inch."

    old "It's like I taught you nothing."
    new "It's like I taught you nothing."

    old "But he had."
    new "But he had."

    old "Sarah knew that a spike was a poor attack, because it took a long time to produce the spell, allowing the other mage to anticipate it."
    new "Sarah knew that a spike was a poor attack, because it took a long time to produce the spell, allowing the other mage to anticipate it."

    old "But she also knew that it sliced through most wards, and forced the other mage to actively catch or deflect it."
    new "But she also knew that it sliced through most wards, and forced the other mage to actively catch or deflect it."

    old "Meaning, that if only for a moment, he had to release his hand from Razaphel."
    new "Meaning, that if only for a moment, he had to release his hand from Razaphel."

    old "Sarah watched as the spirit leapt up, free from his torture. The thing's mouth opened like a snake, rows and rows of fangs emerging."
    new "Sarah watched as the spirit leapt up, free from his torture. The thing's mouth opened like a snake, rows and rows of fangs emerging."

    old "On Xan's face, she could see that the mage had realized his mistake by the shadow that the spirit now cast over him."
    new "On Xan's face, she could see that the mage had realized his mistake by the shadow that the spirit now cast over him."

    old "Razaphel's mouth clamped shut, the rows of teeth catching Xan by his collarbone."
    new "Razaphel's mouth clamped shut, the rows of teeth catching Xan by his collarbone."

    old "Sarah watched."
    new "Sarah watched."

    old "Xan's entire head was gone, dissapeared into the mouth of the spirit. A muffled scream could be heard emerging from within."
    new "Xan's entire head was gone, dissapeared into the mouth of the spirit. A muffled scream could be heard emerging from within."

    old "She watched as Xan tried to drive the spirit away, flailing his remaining arm with burning magic."
    new "She watched as Xan tried to drive the spirit away, flailing his remaining arm with burning magic."

    old "But the spirit could tolerate the pain, because it knew victory was near."
    new "But the spirit could tolerate the pain, because it knew victory was near."

    old "Sarah watched Xan's body slow down. His flailing turned to twitching, until eventually, even that ceased."
    new "Sarah watched Xan's body slow down. His flailing turned to twitching, until eventually, even that ceased."

    old "With a loud crunch, Razaphel's jaws broke through the last of Xan's resistance, snapping his bones and tearing off his head."
    new "With a loud crunch, Razaphel's jaws broke through the last of Xan's resistance, snapping his bones and tearing off his head."

    old "Xan's body collapsed to the floor with a solid thud."
    new "Xan's body collapsed to the floor with a solid thud."

    old "Sarah forced herself to look at her former mentor. She had caused this, wanted this. What right did she then have to now look away?"
    new "Sarah forced herself to look at her former mentor. She had caused this, wanted this. What right did she then have to now look away?"

    old "Blood flowed freely from the stump on Xan's body, splattering the floor in blood. It didn't take long for the blood to darken and stain."
    new "Blood flowed freely from the stump on Xan's body, splattering the floor in blood. It didn't take long for the blood to darken and stain."

    old "Hovering over his body, the spirit."
    new "Hovering over his body, the spirit."

    old "It is done."
    new "It is done."

    old "There was little more to say."
    new "There was little more to say."

    old "Sarah had thought she would feel some kind of release, knowing she was free, but the act itself and its brutality had stripped her of that."
    new "Sarah had thought she would feel some kind of release, knowing she was free, but the act itself and its brutality had stripped her of that."

    old "Still, no matter how deep or far she searched her heart and soul, she found no regret. No secret wish to undo what she had done."
    new "Still, no matter how deep or far she searched her heart and soul, she found no regret. No secret wish to undo what she had done."

    old "It is done..."
    new "It is done..."

    old "Now you have your freedom."
    new "Now you have your freedom."

    old "So the question of now what is one you will have to answer for yourself."
    new "So the question of now what is one you will have to answer for yourself."

    old "And our deal?"
    new "And our deal?"

    old "Our deal stands. I have fulfilled my end, and one day you will fulfill yours."
    new "Our deal stands. I have fulfilled my end, and one day you will fulfill yours."

    old "Sarah had imagined the spirit might want her, seize her this very moment, but she understood that was foolish of her to think."
    new "Sarah had imagined the spirit might want her, seize her this very moment, but she understood that was foolish of her to think."

    old "The spirit had not risked everything for a chance to have her body. His demand, if it ever came, would be far more costly."
    new "The spirit had not risked everything for a chance to have her body. His demand, if it ever came, would be far more costly."

    old "Sarah stood up and carefully stepped over the body, avoiding any blood."
    new "Sarah stood up and carefully stepped over the body, avoiding any blood."

    old "One advice, Sarah..."
    new "One advice, Sarah..."

    old "Take the fate stone and carry it through the house. Hold it up in every corner, and it will shroud the house from the eyes of the gods."
    new "Take the fate stone and carry it through the house. Hold it up in every corner, and it will shroud the house from the eyes of the gods."

    old "And perhaps more acutely, shroud it from the mage's order."
    new "And perhaps more acutely, shroud it from the mage's order."

    old "In all the hurry, Sarah had not given much thought to what came after, or whether Xan's order might come after her."
    new "In all the hurry, Sarah had not given much thought to what came after, or whether Xan's order might come after her."

    old "Do you think they will come for me?"
    new "Do you think they will come for me?"

    old "The spirit twirled, seeming unconcerned."
    new "The spirit twirled, seeming unconcerned."

    old "Perhaps, or perhaps not. Their order is often hard to understand."
    new "Perhaps, or perhaps not. Their order is often hard to understand."

    old "But with the fate stone, you will cut out their most powerful tool, the eyes of the gods."
    new "But with the fate stone, you will cut out their most powerful tool, the eyes of the gods."

    old "Without it, they can find you no easier than any ordinary mortal can. And this house, they will never find."
    new "Without it, they can find you no easier than any ordinary mortal can. And this house, they will never find."

    old "This gave Sarah some comfort."
    new "This gave Sarah some comfort."

    old "The house had been a safe haven for her, and now, it could still be so."
    new "The house had been a safe haven for her, and now, it could still be so."

    old "Her house, she corrected herself. It all belonged to her now."
    new "Her house, she corrected herself. It all belonged to her now."

    old "She left the spirit without further words and did as instructed, carrying the fate stone throughout every room, warding the house."
    new "She left the spirit without further words and did as instructed, carrying the fate stone throughout every room, warding the house."

    old "Near the end, exhausted, she returned to her room."
    new "Near the end, exhausted, she returned to her room."

    old "Sarah dragged her feet as she walked into her bedroom."
    new "Sarah dragged her feet as she walked into her bedroom."

    old "The events of only a moment ago now feeling like a strange dream."
    new "The events of only a moment ago now feeling like a strange dream."

    old "Only the bruises on her body reminded her it was real."
    new "Only the bruises on her body reminded her it was real."

    old "Sarah looked at her bed."
    new "Sarah looked at her bed."

    old "Samayra was sound asleep, despite everything."
    new "Samayra was sound asleep, despite everything."

    old "Sarah envied her."
    new "Sarah envied her."

    old "Climbing into the bed next to Samayra, Sarah pulled herself closer, allowing herself to feel Samayra's body against her own."
    new "Climbing into the bed next to Samayra, Sarah pulled herself closer, allowing herself to feel Samayra's body against her own."

    old "She felt Samayra begin to stir, but not quite wake up."
    new "She felt Samayra begin to stir, but not quite wake up."

    old "Her lithe frame. Her warm body. Her near perfect shape."
    new "Her lithe frame. Her warm body. Her near perfect shape."

    old "I'm a terrible person."
    new "I'm a terrible person."

    old "Sarah whispered into Samayra's ear."
    new "Sarah whispered into Samayra's ear."

    old "Sarah held onto her, fearing that if she were to let go, she might lose one of the few things that remained to her."
    new "Sarah held onto her, fearing that if she were to let go, she might lose one of the few things that remained to her."

    old "As that fear grew, Sarah slowly slipped into a deep sleep."
    new "As that fear grew, Sarah slowly slipped into a deep sleep."

    old "Empty."
    new "Empty."

    old "Alone, said a voice in her head."
    new "Alone, said a voice in her head."

    old "Sarah shook her head and let herself fall into the bed."
    new "Sarah shook her head and let herself fall into the bed."

    old "Sleep."
    new "Sleep."

    old "After all of this, she would need a year worth of sleep."
    new "After all of this, she would need a year worth of sleep."

    old "Not long after, Sarah slipped into a deep sleep."
    new "Not long after, Sarah slipped into a deep sleep."

